234f67b4-f632-46cb-a6cc-6178b0d74e31.09993f49-9253-4cd0-8825-59e8d546084b.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults". As a result, the context key whose name is in the keyName input will be appended with the string from the input resultText.

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Returns\:
The the value of the context variable it appended to.

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

234f67b4-f632-46cb-a6cc-6178b0d74e31.2147c4d8-8283-42a1-a309-5c281eb2603a.description=
Iterates through a list of values. If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list.

Inputs\:
separator - The list separator (or delimiter).
list - The list to be split

Responses\:
has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned.
failure - failed to process the list.
no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list.

Returns\:
The current element of the list, if the response is has more

234f67b4-f632-46cb-a6cc-6178b0d74e31.963aed76-f5fa-4805-9c4a-80da2e07b23a.description=
Synopsis

    This operator executes a command from the command line of a remote action server (RAS).

Inputs

    ipAddress - The IP address of the LIF (required).
    netMask - The net mask of the IP address (required).
    command - The command to execute.
    pyLibPath - 
    arguments - Any variables (data) to use in the command.
    environment - Specifies environment variables/values that need to be defined when running the command.
    path - The path to the command's executable file.
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: None.

     cmd_timeout - Timeout in milliseconds before the command is considered failed when returnImmediately is false.
       Valid values\: Positive number miliseconds.
       Default value\: 100000 (100 seconds).

    returnImmediately - If true, the operation will execute the command and return immediately.  It will not wait for the command to finish.
       Valid values\: true, false.
       Default value\: false.

Results

    STDOUT - The standard output of the command.
    STDERR - The standard error output of the command.

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Failure - Some operations and/or subflows failed.

Notes

    1. On unix we cannot mandate what type of shell to be used (sh, bash, ksh, csh, etc), so be sure to include the shell in your command
         if you need things like file redirection.
           Example\:
           sh -c "ls -lha /etc > /tmp/myfile"
    2. On Windows, this command will prepend cmd.exe /C or command.exe /C to the command you specify, so there is no need to pass that into this operation.

234f67b4-f632-46cb-a6cc-6178b0d74e31.fff20647-e864-4bcf-969d-7d25fab06c3a.description=
Synopsis

    This operator executes a command from the command line of a remote action server (RAS).

Inputs

    ipAddress - The IP address of the LIF (required).
    netMask - The net mask of the IP address (required).
    command - The command to execute.
    pyLibPath - 
    arguments - Any variables (data) to use in the command.
    environment - Specifies environment variables/values that need to be defined when running the command.
    path - The path to the command's executable file.
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: None.

     cmd_timeout - Timeout in milliseconds before the command is considered failed when returnImmediately is false.
       Valid values\: Positive number miliseconds.
       Default value\: 100000 (100 seconds).

    returnImmediately - If true, the operation will execute the command and return immediately.  It will not wait for the command to finish.
       Valid values\: true, false.
       Default value\: false.

Results

    STDOUT - The standard output of the command.
    STDERR - The standard error output of the command.

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Failure - Some operations and/or subflows failed.

Notes

    1. On unix we cannot mandate what type of shell to be used (sh, bash, ksh, csh, etc), so be sure to include the shell in your command
         if you need things like file redirection.
           Example\:
           sh -c "ls -lha /etc > /tmp/myfile"
    2. On Windows, this command will prepend cmd.exe /C or command.exe /C to the command you specify, so there is no need to pass that into this operation.
